<br>
In Nightmare, Justice, Disease and Innovation the epic performs extremely well still. With the additon of Fists of Ixiblat, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>George the Jibober</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is doing very well. Often hunt with groups only having a shaman for semi Crowd Control, standard tactic is to use <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>George</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to sic on adds, or to fire into a heavy pull to absorb some aggro for healers/debuffers afore they go to work.<br>
Usually by time we finish one mob, epic has done considerable damage to an add. PoP mobs, while hitting hard, don't have the ludicrous hit points/AC of luclin mobs (slow is gud!)<br>
Frequently, good use of pet has saved the group, like 4 pulls of nightstalkers in PoN with no mezzer. <br>
<br>
Using Mend Companion skill and if needed chain 52/44 pet heals, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>George</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> can do pretty well, and if mob is slowed, very well. Using that and the MASSIVE aggro generated by Firebolt of Talon and crystalline silken nets, mages can provide very useful semi-CC abilities.<br>
<br>
Firebolt of Talon *OWNS* for several reasons: <br>
1) horses, most of PoP is outdoors, so you *SHOULD* get a horse ASAP. THis gives superb mana regen and HIGH vantage point to launch bolts.<br>
2) Aggro, although this is a real problem with FoT, I use the extreme aggro it generates to aggro off clerics etc in emergency and run round like a demented chicken with the mob on my heels <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    This can save your group.<br>
3) Using FoT with mana-regen means like a horse, plus right click nuke items, you can do extremely efficient fast damage. Shock of Fiery Blades is far far less aggro than FoT, and for conjuration specialists, much more efficient. However mana regen is often less of a hassle than getting mobs dead *fast*. I only have FT1, but I usually find on PoP mobs, 2 Boots of Blade Calling nukes, then a FoT, then perhaps another BoBC nuke is efficient and *FUN*. I can do that on every mob unless pulls are especially fast, and stay around 90 mana. Thats very good damage output. The huge DPs potential of FoT is great when you want hard hiting PoP mobs deaf *FAST*.<br>
I use SoFB in areas where mobs are mezzed or for efficiency if a pull is very heavy and I need to maximize efficiency and have low aggro by churnining out nuke after nuke after nuke.... You want something dead fast, 3 FoT up its ass and kite round camp if need to survive ensuing hate hehe.<br>
<br>
<br>
--POP PETS--<br>
ok, on high con mobs, on raids, in PoV and up, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>BE PREPARED TO FORGET THE EPIC!</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> it is just not good enough. Test for yourself in what areas and on what mobs epic pet's proc lands. I've used 61 air and found it very good and its casts and procs *LAND* on a host of various mobs.<br>
have chain casted it a fair bit to deal with bad pulls etc. Very nice pet, regen is good at saving mana for healing.<br>
  --I think pet regen is based on LEVEL, hence epic summoned with Gloves of Dark Summoning regens fast because it's a lvl 50+ mob! Remember pets lvl 39+ regenning faster?--<br>
<br>
--The Fist of Ixiblat --<br>
spell is a real boon, don't need to buy gnoll hide whips by pack load unless i real want to use them <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
As usual, procs are very random, but sweet when you see a string of procs. hand these out to other pet casters in groups for real nice damage improvement, watch for all them flame effects as procs go off!<br>
<br>
--Servant of Ro--<br>
Ok this would be good if it cast a DD and was a high con pet. Found it's pretty good when leaving pet on an add to also have servant on the add to, servant never seems to draw aggro unless mob is reooted nearby or its only thing around. Also kiting mobs in circle around Servant lets it fire away at will, which again works good in some scenarios.<br>
Servant does need to be made lvl 60 though so it can land nukes.<br>
When using it , move out of way so pet has line of sight to target so it's bolts hit.<br>
<br>
--Tiny Companion--<br>
Ok this is DERN sweet! Bolt spells from you and Servant of Ro are blocked by tall things so...shrink pet! also epic and high lvl pets are damn big.<br>
<br>
--COH NERFS--<br>
These are a real pain in ass, especially due to the graveyards. graveards NEED TO FIXED! Effect should be triggerable by you, as is, raids get split up as bodies yanked to GY, if tha thappens to wrong persron , raid is often screwed totally<br>
Jopefully CoH will be fixed so it can't be used in certain EVENT areas so folk cant exploit. As is the nerfs are VERY annoying.<br>
<br>
--MOB RESISTS--<br>
Wow, while there are variations in resists (PoI magic nukes tends to hit better etc), mobs seem to have reasonable resists, this is nice. While we dont have the extremely low resistsof Lucin, what we do have is (so far) interestingly annoying without being painful (ie you'll find some mobs resisting but it's usually logical or as a typical amount thats not too bad..remember Velious anyone? Now THAT was sucky for resists)<br>
<br>
--MAGE ROLE'--<br>
Mages role in PoP IS as damage dealers. Fair amount of summoned creatures so far, antisummoned spells work VERY well on them now due to resist changes. Hey, Turn Summoned rocks in PoJ execution trial! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
Unless your guild has VT items, mage focus summons become once again useful and needed.<br>
Having a pet that can enrage is fun <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
Mages ARE wanted as damage dealers.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Just some thoughts <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
